The fire at the Majuba power station in Mpumalanga has been extinguished. JOHANNESBURG - A fire at Eskom's Majuba power station has been extinguished. There were no injuries reported. READ: Police investigating suspected sabotage at Eskom The power utility said in a statement that coal delivery to the power station has been impacted. The cause of the fire remains unknown. Eskom says the facility has to cool down before a forensic investigation can begin.